00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,200
A parrot would be awesome.
养只鹦鹉会很酷。

174
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,200
I'll tell you what.
我跟你说吧。

175
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:54,640
I can get you some hamsters, and we'll take it from there.
我可以给你买几只仓鼠，然后我们再慢慢来。

176
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:56,080
Yay!
耶！

177
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,700
All right.
好吧。

178
00:06:58,700 --> 00:06:59,700
We're back.
我们回来了。

179
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:02,480
We've picked out four key phrases for you.
我们为你挑选了四个关键短语。

180
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:06,640
Let's take a look at those now in Fluency Builder.
现在让我们在流利度训练中看看这些。

181
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:07,640
Fluency Builder.
流利度提升。

182
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:13,360
So at the very beginning of today's conversation, we hear the first person say, we've been over
所以在今天对话的开头，我们听到第一个人说，“我们讨论过”

183
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:16,200
this a hundred times.
这件事一百遍了。

184
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,840
So what does this mean?
那么这是什么意思呢？

185
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:19,960
This means that they've never talked about this before?
这是说他们以前从没讨论过这件事吗？

186
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:25,840
No, this is actually the opposite, but it's a way to exaggerate, right?
不，实际上恰恰相反，但这是一种夸张的说法，对吧？

187
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:29,800
Because obviously they haven't maybe talked about getting a pet a hundred times, but you're
因为显然他们可能没有真的讨论过养宠物一百次，但你

188
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:35,160
just making emphasis on the fact that we've talked about this many, many, many times.
只是在强调我们讨论过很多很多次这个事实。

189
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:37,200
And almost like you're tired of it.
而且几乎像是你对此感到厌烦了。

190
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:40,560
Like, oh, do we have to talk about this again?
就像，哦，我们非得再谈这个吗？

191
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:44,080
It's like you said, an exaggeration to say, come on.
就像你说的，是一种夸张，意思是“拜托”。

192
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:47,160
So we've been over this a million times.
所以我们讨论过这件事一百万遍了。

193
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:49,560
We've been over this a hundred times.
我们讨论过这件事一百遍了。

194
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:52,640
These are all ways of saying, oh, we have to talk about this again?
这些都是表达“哦，我们还得再谈这个吗？”的方式。

195
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:53,640
Exactly.
没错。

196
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:57,440
So you're emphasizing that, well, maybe you've done it too many times already.
所以你在强调，嗯，也许你已经做过太多次了。

197
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:58,440
All right.
好的。

198
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:02,440
And well, when they were talking about the puppy or the kitty, the guy asked, well, who's
嗯，当他们谈论小狗或小猫时，那个男的问，“那谁来”

199
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:05,280
going to look after the dog or the cat?
照顾狗或猫呢？

200
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,280
Okay.
好的。

201
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:07,560
So this is an important phrase.
所以这是一个重要的短语。

202
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:10,520
We're going to treat this as a kind of a chunk.
我们要把它当作一个整体来对待。

203
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:13,100
These words go together, to look after.
这些词是连在一起的，“to look after”。

204
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:16,880
So we could look after a baby or look after the pet.
所以我们可以说照顾婴儿或照顾宠物。

205
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:19,360
This means to watch or to care for.
这意味着照看或照料。

206
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,360
Right.
对。

207
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,360
To take care.
照顾。

208
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:25,600
So maybe if you're going to go out tonight, you want to leave your son with a babysitter
所以如果你今晚要出去，你可能想把儿子留给保姆

209
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,080
to look after him.
来照看他。

210
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:28,080
Right.
对。

211
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:32,280
To make sure that there are no problems or to make sure that he eats and goes to sleep.
确保没有麻烦，或者确保他吃饭和睡觉。

212
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:33,280
Exactly.
没错。

213
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:37,200
So to look after, to take care or to make sure he or she is okay.
所以“to look after”就是照顾或确保他或她没事。

214
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,400
All right.
好的。

215
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:40,280
And well, obviously the guy didn't want a puppy.
显然，那个家伙不想要小狗。

216
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:41,520
He didn't want a kitty.
他不想要小猫。

217
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:46,200
So the girl was giving alternatives and said, well, how about we get a cat or a ferret?
所以女孩在提供替代方案，说，那我们养只猫或雪貂怎么样？

218
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,200
Okay.
好的。

219
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:50,000
The phrase here, how about, is very, very common in English.
这里的短语“how about”在英语中非常非常常见。

220
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:54,440
I think a lot of people who learn English have a hard time knowing when to use this
我觉得很多学英语的人很难知道什么时候用这个。

221
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,440
phrase.
短语。

222
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,440
How about?
怎么样？

223
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:57,960
That's right.
没错。

224
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,280
So it's very simple.
所以这很简单。

225
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:03,520
The phrase how about is to give an alternative.
短语“怎么样”是用来提出一个替代方案。

226
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,520
Right.
对。

227
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:05,520
Okay.
好的。

228
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:06,520
Or a suggestion.
或者一个建议。

229
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:10,040
So for example, you and I are talking about where to eat lunch.
比如，你和我正在讨论去哪里吃午饭。

230
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:11,040
I don't know.
我不知道。

231
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:12,040
And you give a suggestion.
然后你提出一个建议。

232
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,040
You say, how about pizza?
你说，吃披萨怎么样？

233
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,420
And I say, I don't know.
然后我说，我不知道。

234
00:09:14,420 --> 00:09:16,160
How about McDonald's?
吃麦当劳怎么样？

235
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:20,120
We're giving suggestions or offering alternatives.
我们在提出建议或提供替代方案。

236
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,120
Exactly.
正是。

237
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:24,440
So this is the correct way of using how about.
所以这是使用“怎么样”的正确方式。

238
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:29,760
Many students make the mistake of using it as to say, how was it?
很多学生会犯错误，把它用成“它怎么样？”。

239
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:31,400
Or how did it go?
或者“进行得怎么样？”。

240
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:32,400
Right?
对吧？

241
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,400
Right.
没错。

242
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,400
So how was your weekend?
那你周末过得怎么样？

243
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,520
That's correct.
这就对了。

244
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:37,160
How about your weekend?
你周末怎么样？

245
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,160
That's incorrect.
那不对。

246
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:39,160
No, do not say that.
不，别那么说。

247
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:41,280
You want to say, how about this?
你应该说，这个怎么样？

248
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,280
How about that?
那个怎么样？

249
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:43,280
How about a Coke?
来杯可乐怎么样？

250
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:44,920
How about some food?
来点吃的怎么样？

251
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:49,680
These are suggestions, but a real question you have to say how was or how is.
这些是建议，但真正的问句你得说“how was”或“how is”。

252
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:50,680
Right.
没错。

253
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:53,280
So never, never, never say, how about your weekend?
所以永远、永远、永远别说“how about your weekend？”

254
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,360
That is incorrect.
那是不对的。

255
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:56,720
And it's actually very common to hear this from students.
而且实际上经常听到学生这么说。

256
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:58,840
So remember, it's not correct.
所以记住，那是不正确的。

257
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:00,040
How about your weekend?
你周末怎么样？

258
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:01,040
No, incorrect.
不，不对。

259
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:03,560
So at the very end of the dialogue, we're talking about hamsters.
在对话的最后，我们谈到了仓鼠。

260
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:07,360
I can get you some hamsters and we'll take it from there.
我可以给你弄几只仓鼠，然后我们再看情况。

261
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,360
That's right.
没错。

262
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,100
The phrase take it from there.
短语“take it from there”。

263
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:14,640
It's kind of a way of saying, look, let's start with something small or let's start
这有点像在说，看，我们先从小事开始，或者从简单的事开始，

264
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:18,580
with something simple and we will see how it goes.
然后看看进展如何。

265
00:10:18,580 --> 00:10:21,720
So basically the woman is saying, I don't want to commit.
所以基本上那个女人在说，我不想承诺。

266
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:27,420
I don't want to agree to get a big animal like a dog or a cat because I'm not sure how
我不想同意养像狗或猫这样的大动物，因为我不确定

267
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:28,420
it will be.
会是什么情况。

268
00:10:28,420 --> 00:10:31,280
I'm not sure if it will be too much responsibility.
我不确定责任会不会太大。

269
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:35,960
So she's saying, okay, we'll get something small and then we'll wait and we'll see what
所以她说，好吧，我们先养个小东西，然后等等看

270
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:36,960
happens.
会发生什么。

271
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:37,960
We'll take it from there.
我们再看情况。

272
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:38,960
That's right.
没错。

273
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:41,880
So it's basically saying, let's start slowly.
所以这基本上就是说，我们慢慢开始。

274
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:47,440
So for example, maybe a guy asks you out and says, hey, will you marry me?
比如，也许一个男的约你出去，说，嘿，你愿意嫁给我吗？

275
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:48,800
And you say, whoa.
然后你说，哇。

276
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:51,960
Let's go on a date first and we'll take it from there.
我们先约会一次，然后再说。

277
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,960
Exactly.
正是。

278
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:53,960
We'll see what happens.
我们看看会发生什么。

279
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,460
So let's start slowly.
所以我们慢慢来。

280
00:10:55,460 --> 00:10:57,760
Let's take things step by step.
我们一步一步来。

281
00:10:57,760 --> 00:10:58,760
All right.
好了。

282
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:01,080
So that's all the phrases that we have for you today.
这就是我们今天为你准备的所有短语。

283
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:04,960
I think we should listen to the dialogue one last time and we'll be back to talk a little
我觉得我们应该再听一遍对话，然后回来再聊

284
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:12,400
bit more.
一点。

285
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:14,200
We've been over this a hundred times.
这事我们已经讨论过一百遍了。

286
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:16,320
We are not getting a pet.
我们不养宠物。

287
